Nelvaan is an icy planet in the Koobi system in the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Nelvaanian people. It is a primitive world of low gravity experiencing the onset of an ice age. Three moons orbit Nelvaan. It is in close proximity to Tythe. A world without a terrible amount of gravity, it is home to several massive life forms, including the vicious Horax.

Nelvaan is also dominated by a landscape of precarious mesas that would have fallen in standard gravity worlds. These mesas are home to the primitive Nelvaanians - blue-furred ursine humanoids. Lacking a planetary government and they held no allegiance to either the Separatists or Republic. It is a rarely visited world useful only to Bothans, who regularly siphon water from the glacial fields, a practice that do not concern the Nelvaanians.

Rodia, an industrial planet in the Tyrius system in the Mid Rim, is the homeworld to the Rodians, being the birthworld of the bounty hunter Greedo the Younger.

Rodia is a hot, humid world which is covered in dense tropical jungles as well as sprawling cities and industrial areas. A large area of the planet is also covered in oceans and there appears to be two polar regions on the extreme latitudes. A known body of water on the planet is the Wesessa Sea where the An'yettu Islands are located.

Two major cities on the planet are Equator City and Iskaayuma which are the planetary capitals at different periods in Rodia's history. Equator City is the traditional capital until Navik the Red usurped control over the planet and moved the capital to his clan's settlement at Iskaayuma. Two known continents are Encheeko and Betu.

Falleen is a planet in the Mid Rim region and home to the Falleen species. It has jungles, vast plains, and icy mountains.

Falleen joined the Galactic Republic circa 3,996 BBY. In the years following the Battle of Naboo, Falleen experienced a boom in the construction of factories and manufacturing facilities, as corporations found it was less costly to maintain such facilities on remote planets. During the Clone Wars, the planet was represented in the Galactic Senate by Zurros, who served as a double agent for Count Dooku until Falleen openly joined the Confederacy.

Later, during the early years of the New Order, Darth Vader established a bacteriological research outpost on the planet. When a highly-destructive bacterium got loose in 7 BBY, Vader ordered his ships in orbit to raze the laboratory and the city surrounding it in order to save the rest of the planet. Vader wiped out the bacterium, along with an entire city and over two hundred thousand Falleen, including the royal House Sizhran. However, biological and chemical research for military purposes continuedon the planet in other locations.

Geonosis is the home planet of the Geonosians and the Confederacy's first capital and a major droid foundry.

Geonosis has a large diameter but light gravity and dense atmosphere. With a weak magnetic field, harsh solar radiation storms are common, and on occasion mass extinctions occurred. The most persistent surface organisms are humble red rock algae while the semi-insectoid Geonosians were driven underground. It consists of a diminutive molten core with a rocky mantle forming a rocky, desert world subject to flash floods that carved great highland canyons. Water makes up 5% of the surface.

Tatooine is a desert world in a binary star system in the Arkanis Sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

It is inhabited by poor locals who mostly farmed moisture for a living. Other activities include used equipment retailing and scrap dealing. The planet is on the 5709-DC Shipping Lane, a spur of the Triellus Trade Route, which itself connects to the Sisar Run. The planet is not far from the Corellian Run. It has its own navigation system. However, it stills play a role in galactic events, serving as the home of Anakin Skywalker. It is here that Jedi Master Qui-Gon Jinn recognized Anakin's potential to become a Jedi and where he introduced him to Obi-Wan Kenobi, his future master and mentor. Tatooine is also the home of Anakin's son, Luke, where he lived until his early adulthood.

Ryloth, also known as Twi'lek, is the harsh, rocky homeworld of the Twi'leks, an Outer Rim Territories world located on the Corellian Run and forming one endpoint of the Death Wind Corridor. Its day and year are identical, so that one side perpetually faced its sun and the other remains in darkness, a phenomenon known as tidal locking. The dayside is referred to as the Bright Lands and the night-side is known as the Darkside.

Bothawui is a cosmopolitan planet, located in the center of Bothan Space of the Mid Rim. It is the homeworld of the Bothan race as well as a major hub for information trafficking. It is also the center of the Bothan Spynet, widely agreed upon to be the best network of information gathering in the the Galaxy. The Imperial name for the planet is Bothawui Proper. The planet is home to both industry and grain farms. The planet is also mined for indigenous ores such as lidium.

The planet was an old member of the Galactic Republic: Bothese is one of the languages from which Basic developed. The Bothans colonized many nearby worlds and Bothawui became the capital of Bothan Sector.

In the years preceding the Clone Wars, the planet was represented in the Galactic Senate by Polo Se'Lab. It remained neutral during the Clone Wars.

Hypori is a temperate planet of small oceans and rocky landscapes located in the Arkanis Sector of the Outer Rim Territories, notable for being a heavy battle droid producer.

The planet had no native population, but following the Invasion of Naboo, Hypori was transformed into a foundry world for the Confederacy of Independent Systems. The planet was located near Geonosis, another world hosting Techno Union droid factories, and an entire hive of Geonosian workers was relocated to Hypori in a sponsored effort by Baktoid Armor Workshop to construct and maintain the new Separatist facilities. The tough bedrock and soil proved difficult to assimilate into a true and proper hive-mound, though the Geonosian workers eventually created huge underground factories. The existence of these droid factories was kept secret from the Galactic Republic during the leadup to the Clone Wars.

Kamino is the watery world where the Clone Army for the Galactic Republic was created and the Kamino home fleet. It is inhabited by a race of tall, elegant beings called the Kaminoans, who kept to themselves and were known for their cloning technology. Kamino is located just south of the Rishi Maze. Kamino is ruled by the ruling council, the only publicly known person of which is Lama Su.

The planet is composed of a molten core with a rocky mantle and silicate rock crust. Climatic change has long ago submerged the planet's continents, drowning the planet under a global ocean that covers 100% of the surface. It is subject to savage storms and powerful lightning bursts that can be seen from orbit.

Ukio is a well-known agriworld in the Ukio system of the Abrion Sector, and homeworld of the Ukians. It serves as one of the top producers of foodstuffs. It is a large planet with a gentle climate due to a low axial tilt, which allows for nearly year-round growing season for agriculture. Nearly the entire planet has been converted to food production uses, and Ukian law even requires crop rotation procedures to maximize output. The planet has three large continents, cut through by hundreds of rivers to provide for natural irrigation. The world is governed by the Overliege, a hereditary monarch.

The planet seceded from the Galactic Republic 22 BBY, shortly before the Clone Wars. At the time, it was ruled by Overliege Topas dosLa, who wanted his world to have better control over its exports and to no longer suffer under burdensome Republic tariffs. It is part of the Galactic Empire now, and many native Humans join the military, including Corporal Oberk, Corporal Janse, and Sergeant Narthax.

Gamorr is the agrarian homeworld of the pig-faced Gamorreans, located in the Opoku system of the Outer Rim. 

Its varied terrain ranges from frozen tundra to deep forests, and is considered quite pleasant by off-worlders. Nevertheless, tourism was highly discouraged to Gamorr because of the vicious lifestyle of ferocious, bloody warfare constantly being waged between rival Gamorrean clans. Prominent mushrooms are also found on Gamorr.
